# LF Studio — Cursor AI Rules (Vibecoding)
# Next.js 16 App Router · React 18 · TypeScript 5.5 · Tailwind CSS v4 · Framer Motion 12

## Project Identity
AI-augmented design agency portfolio. Single-page homepage + /about + /project/[slug] case studies.
All homepage content uses server components wrapping client-section components.

---

## Stack Rules

- **Next.js 16 App Router ONLY** — no Pages Router patterns
- **Tailwind CSS v4** — use `@theme` for tokens, NOT `tailwind.config.ts`
  - Brand tokens: `bg-lf-cream`, `bg-lf-green`, `text-lf-ink`, `text-lf-green-bright`
  - CSS linter may flag `@theme`, `@source`, `@custom-variant`, `@apply` — these are VALID Tailwind v4 syntax, not errors
- **Framer Motion**: import from `"motion/react"` (v12 package name), NOT `"framer-motion"`
- **TypeScript strict mode** — no implicit any

---

## File & Folder Naming Conventions

| Type | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| React components | PascalCase.tsx | `HeroSection.tsx`, `AiEfficiencySection.tsx` |
| Data files | camelCase + Data suffix | `portfolioData.ts`, `servicesData.ts` |
| Hooks | camelCase + use prefix | `useInView.ts`, `useScramble.ts` |
| Utilities | camelCase | `img.ts`, `utils.ts` |
| Public folders & image files | kebab-case | `service-images/`, `business-collaterals.png` |
| `src/assets/` hash files | **DO NOT rename** | `01e9fb8693b4b3c1.png` |

**NEVER create files or folders with spaces in the name.**

---

## Directory Map (Quick Reference)

```
src/app/                    — Next.js routes (page.tsx, layout.tsx, route.ts)
src/components/layout/     — Navbar, ContactSection, GifPreloader, ElasticDivider
src/components/sections/   — Homepage section components (one section = one file)
src/components/pages/      — Full-page wrappers (AboutPage, ProjectDetailPage)
src/components/ui/         — shadcn/ui primitives — do NOT modify
src/components/figma/      — Figma-generated utility components
src/data/                  — Single source of truth for all content (edit here only)
src/assets/                — Figma-exported images; hash-named files MUST NOT be renamed
src/imports/               — Auto-generated Figma SVG path data; do not edit manually
src/hooks/                 — Custom React hooks
src/lib/                   — Utilities: imgSrc(), cn()
src/types/                 — TypeScript declarations
public/images/             — Static images (service-images/, efficiency/, faster-section/)
public/portfolio/          — Portfolio thumbnails + detail galleries
```

---

## Critical Patterns

### Image imports from `src/assets/`
Always wrap with `imgSrc()` — returns a plain URL string:
```tsx
import imgFoo from "@/assets/some-image.png";
import { imgSrc } from "@/lib/img";
const url = imgSrc(imgFoo);
```

### Figma asset imports (hash-named files)
```tsx
import img from "figma:asset/01e9fb8693b4b3c1ba8fff50a7a6d95ec10e880a.png";
// Resolves via webpack plugin in next.config.ts → src/assets/{hash}.png
// NEVER rename hash files — they are keyed by content hash
```

### Public images
Use plain string paths — no import needed:
```tsx
src="/images/service-images/business-collaterals.png"
src="/portfolio/portfolio_section/second_look_1x.webp"
```

### Sticky card stack (`ServiceDetailCards`)
ALL cards MUST be direct siblings inside ONE `<section>` element.
CSS sticky only sticks within the nearest scrolling ancestor.
Never wrap individual cards in their own positioned containers.

### Tab auto-cycling pattern
Both `AiEfficiencySection` and `TestimonialsSection` use:
```tsx
useEffect(() => {
  timerRef.current = setTimeout(advanceTab, AUTO_CYCLE_MS);
  return () => clearTimeout(timerRef.current);
}, [activeTab, advanceTab]);
```
Click handlers must `clearTimeout` before `setActiveTab` to reset the timer.

### Portfolio slug routing
`portfolioItems[].slug` in `src/data/portfolioData.ts` MUST exactly match:
- The URL segment in `/project/[slug]`
- The key in `projectGallery` map in `ProjectDetailPage.tsx`

Current slugs: `second-look-health`, `antaranga-ai`, `frogtoberfest`, `minimeals`

### `"use client"` directive
Add to any component using: `useState`, `useEffect`, `useRef`, event handlers,
`motion` components from `motion/react`, `useRouter`, `usePathname`.
Server components (no directive needed): `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, static data rendering.

---

## Data Editing Rules

**NEVER edit content inside component files.** Always edit `src/data/*.ts`:

| File | Controls |
|---|---|
| `portfolioData.ts` | Portfolio items + case study content |
| `servicesData.ts` | Service card content + images |
| `efficiencyData.ts` | AI efficiency tabs, speedups, descriptions |
| `processData.ts` | Process steps |
| `testimonialsData.ts` | Testimonials carousel + featured |
| `siteConfig.ts` | Nav items, social links, brand config |

---

## Adding New Things

### New homepage section
1. Create `src/components/sections/MyNewSection.tsx` (add `"use client"` if interactive)
2. Add data to `src/data/` or inline if trivial
3. Import + add to `src/app/page.tsx` in correct order
4. Update CLAUDE.md sections table

### New portfolio project
1. Add `PortfolioItem` object to `src/data/portfolioData.ts` (include `slug`)
2. Add gallery images to `public/portfolio/{slug}-details/` (kebab-case folder)
3. Add gallery entry to `projectGallery` map in `src/components/pages/ProjectDetailPage.tsx`
4. Add thumbnail to `public/portfolio/portfolio_section/{slug}_1x.webp`

---

## What NOT to Do

- Do NOT add `tailwind.config.ts` — project uses Tailwind v4 `@theme` blocks
- Do NOT rename hash-named files in `src/assets/`
- Do NOT import large layout files from `src/imports/` (they are legacy) — only the `svg-*.ts` files there are in use
- Do NOT use `next/image` unless images have known dimensions (project uses `<img>` + `imgSrc()`)
- Do NOT install `framer-motion` — the package is `motion` (v12), import from `"motion/react"`
- Do NOT edit `src/components/ui/` — regenerate via shadcn CLI if needed
- Do NOT create folders or filenames with spaces
- Do NOT URL-encode paths in source code — rename the file/folder instead
